post1.title: quizz project
post1.content: this is my online quiz coded in python . correct = 0 int(correct) print("question 1: Name the Python output command mentioned in this lesson") answer_1 = input() if answer_1 == "print": print("correct!") correct = correct + 1 else: print("wrong!") print("question 2: If you see many lines of code in order, what would College Board call it?") answer_2 = input() if answer_2 == "sequence": print("correct!") correct = correct + 1 else: print("wrong!") print("question 3: Describe a keyword used in Python to define a function?") answer_3 = input() if answer_3 == "def": print("correct!") correct = correct + 1 else: print("wrong!") print("What command is used to include other functions that were previously developed?") answer_3 = input() if answer_3 == "import": print("correct!") correct = correct + 1 else: print("wrong!") (percentage) = (correct/4)*100 int(percentage) print("you got", correct, "correct!") print(percentage, "%") . question 1: Name the Python output command mentioned in this lesson correct! question 2: If you see many lines of code in order, what would College Board call it? correct! question 3: Describe a keyword used in Python to define a function? correct! What command is used to include other functions that were previously developed? correct! you got 4 correct! 100.0 % .

post2.title: Poem(post In Docx)
post2.content: Either you will . go through this door . or you will not go through. . If you go through . there is always the risk . of remembering your name. . Things look at you doubly . and you must look back . and let them happen. . If you do not go through . it is possible . to live worthily . to maintain your attitudes . to hold your position . to die bravely . but much will blind you, . much will evade you, . at what cost who knows? . The door itself makes no promises. . It is only a door. .
